&lt;p&gt;not hevily used in SWF as generally we recommend decoupling flows from this kind of stuff, but still possible&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="40877" author="sandrews" created="Tue, 4 Nov 2008 08:35:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have implemented these concepts for the spring:url tag for rendering URLs in a JSP.  Perhaps they should be pulled into a common utility class.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Unfortunately, the servletRelative: scheme only works as expected with prefix based servlet mappings (ie &apos;/app/&lt;b&gt;&apos;).  Mappings such as &apos;&lt;/b&gt;.htm&apos; or &apos;/&apos;, do not work as expected.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="62106" author="rstoya05-aop" created="Fri, 7 Jan 2011 09:36:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Web Flow allows embedding variables in the returned location string too (also the subject of &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-2692&quot; title=&quot;RedirectView with more flexible URL-building&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPR-2692&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPR-2692&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;). Currently RedirectView exposes all model attributes by default, which is not enough control and doesn&apos;t work for redirecting via template URLs.&lt;/p&gt;






